                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d382">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5531/801a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-24T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 24, 1939—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>51. Because of Labor Day holiday, it has been decided to extend the time for
                    written statements from September 16 to September 27 and for opening of hearings
                    from October 2 to October 9. These changes in dates were announced August
                    22.</p>
                <pb facs="0440" n="432" xml:id="pg_432"/>
                <p>We therefore expect to be able to make definitive offers of concessions about
                    October 1.6. Meanwhile, we are preparing a reply to the Belgian counter-proposal
                    of general provisions of April 11, 1939, with a text adapted for inclusion in a
                    new trade agreement. This will be mailed in a few days. We also will prepare as
                    soon as possible a tentative list of requests for concessions by Belgium, which
                    will be subject to revision about October 16.</p>
                <p>Please inform Foreign Office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
